; ============================================================================
; OUTBOUND WHITELIST -- who this PBX is allowed to CALL.
;
; Format: one E.164 number per line. E.164 means "+" then country code then
; the rest of the number, no spaces or dashes. Example: +15125551234
;
; Rules:
;   - ";" starts a comment. Everything after ";" on a line is ignored.
;     This means you can label numbers with names:
;         +15125551234   ; Mom mobile
;         +15125559876 ;Dad
;   - Lines that are entirely whitespace or comment are ignored.
;   - A single "*" on its own line means "allow ANY outbound number". This
;     is the escape hatch -- not recommended once you're on a paid account
;     because it disables protection against toll-fraud if someone ever
;     compromises an extension.
;   - Empty file (no allowed numbers) = NO outbound calls. Safe default.
;
; Edits take effect on the NEXT call -- no reload needed.
;
; On a Telnyx TRIAL, only your verified number actually works at Telnyx's
; end anyway, so adding it here is a no-op in practice. Once you upgrade,
; this list becomes your line of defense.
; ============================================================================

; Examples (uncomment + edit):
; +15125551234   ; Mom mobile
; +15555550100   ; Plumber


